# 📚 Book API

A simple RESTful API built with **Express** and **TypeScript** to manage books.  
This project demonstrates basic CRUD-like functionality (currently `GET` and `POST`).

---

## 🚀 Features
- Get all books
- Filter books by author
- Add a new book with validation (title and author required, optional year)

---

## 📦 Installation

Clone the repository and install dependencies:

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd book-api
npm install


▶️ Running the API

Start the development server: npm run dev

By default, the server runs on:

http://localhost:3000

📖 API Endpoints
Get all books
GET http://localhost:3000/books

Get books by author
GET /books?author=James%20Clear

Add a new book
POST /books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Clean Code",
  "author": "Robert C. Martin",
  "year": 2008
}

